snippet.textDisplay: Tune was great. Singer is brilliant. However, not getting the chills. I have visited every single song on mtv coke studio searching for gems to be added to my collection, however I feel like I can only listen to them once or twice. Every song has one thing in common; "a bollywood touch". Sway away from it to preserve the originality and see how this move changes everything. You need to fill your compositions with real soulful music. Ponder for future projects.

snippet.textDisplay: Why is there a discussion going on regarding Pakistan and Indian versions of Coke studio, which one is best? There have been so many episodes of both versions...both are special in their own styles...Pakistani one is more into Traditional styles...Hindustani classical...Rahat was amazing...Arif Lohar was amazing...Indian one is more versatile ranging from classical to funk, jazz rock, electronica and others...both of these versions are a celebration of music only...music which can touch anybody, anywhere...we don't really need to downright compare these two...that doesn't make sense.....and if you really want to listen to Original music collaboration compositions truly of a global nature...shift to Dewarists...that will end the discussion I presume...
